WorkoutName: Barbell Behind The Back Wrist Curl

Instruction.1: Stand straight and hold the barbell behind you using a pronated grip with your hands and feet shoulder-width apart.
Instruction.2: Slowly curl your wrists in a semi-circular motion upwards.
Instruction.3: Hold the barbell at the apex of the motion and then slowly lower the barbell back down to starting position.

Instruction.1: Grab a straight bar with a supinated (underhand) grip.
Instruction.2: Kneel down next to a flat bench and place your forearms on the bench with your wrists just off the bench.
Instruction.3: Let the barbell pull down on your wrists until they are extended.
Instruction.4: Curl the barbell until your wrists are fully flexed.
Instruction.5: Lower in a controlled manner and repeat.

Instruction.1: Take a double overhand grip that's about shoulder width. Flex your elbows while keeping your elbows tucked in. Try not to let them flare out.
Instruction.2: Curl until your forearm presses into your bicep. Then fully extend your elbows at the bottom of each rep.

Instruction.1: Position a barbell in a landmine or corner of a room and stand facing it with your feet shoulder-width apart.
Instruction.2: Grasp the end of the barbell with a neutral grip, keeping your arms straight and your shoulders relaxed.
Instruction.3: Bend at the hips and knees to lower your torso until it is almost parallel to the ground.
Instruction.4: Pull the barbell towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together as you row the weight up.

Instruction.1: Position a barbell in a landmine or corner of a room and stand facing it with your feet shoulder-width apart.
Instruction.2: Grasp the end of the barbell with an overhand grip, keeping your arms straight and your shoulders relaxed.
Instruction.3: Bend at the hips and knees to lower your torso until it is almost parallel to the ground.
Instruction.4: Pull the barbell towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together as you row the weight up.

Instruction.1: Position a barbell in a landmine or corner of a room and stand facing sideways with a staggered stance and your feet shoulder-width apart.
Instruction.2: Grasp the end of the barbell with an overhand grip, keeping your arms straight and your shoulders relaxed.
Instruction.3: Bend at the hips and knees to lower your torso until it is almost parallel to the ground.
Instruction.4: Pull the barbell towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together as you row the weight up.

Instruction.1: Grab the barbell with an overhand grip. Hinge forward while keeping your back flat until your torso is about parallel with the ground.
Instruction.2: Let your arms hang freely.
Instruction.3: Pull the bar to your torso while tucking your elbows in slightly.
Instruction.4: Extend your elbows fully before initiating the next rep.

Instruction.1: Grab a barbell with a shoulder width pronated or supinated grip.
Instruction.2: Bend forward at your hips while maintaining a flat back.
Instruction.3: Pull the weight toward your upper abdomen.
Instruction.4: Lower the weight in a controlled manner and repeat.

Instruction.1: Sit on preacher bench, grip EZ bar overhand at shoulder width, elbows resting on pad.
Instruction.2: Curl bar towards chin, keep elbows stable.
Instruction.3: Lower bar slowly to starting position, maintaining control throughout.

Instruction.1: Grab a barbell with an overhand grip and lay your forearms across a bench.
Instruction.2: Let your wrists flex fully, then extend your wrists.

Instruction.1: Begin by standing with your feet hip-width apart and holding a barbell at one side of your body, with your palms facing your thighs.
Instruction.2: Keeping your core engaged and your back straight, bend at the hips and knees to lower the barbell down towards the ground.
Instruction.3: As the barbell reaches the ground, use your legs and glutes to push through your heels and extend your hips and knees to raise your body back to the starting position.
Instruction.4: Repeat the movement for the desired number of reps, then switch sides and repeat the exercise with the barbell on the opposite side of your body.

Instruction.1: Begin by standing with your feet hip-width apart with the bar on the ground at your side.
Instruction.2: Lift the bar to your side and walk for the allotted amount of time or distance.
Instruction.3: Set the bar down and switch sides.

Instruction.1: Raise your arm to shoulder height at 90 degrees to your body.
Instruction.2: Press lightly on your hand and push towards you.
Instruction.3: Rotate the arm across your body.
Instruction.4: Switch sides and repeat.

Instruction.1: Place your hands together.
Instruction.2: Rotate your arms and hands 180 degrees.
Instruction.3: Hold at the peak of the stretch.
Instruction.4: Return to starting position.

Instruction.1: Place your hand against a wall, palms facing upward, with finger tips touching.
Instruction.2: Slowly lean into your palm.
Instruction.3: Hold at the peak of the stretch.
Instruction.4: Return to starting position.

Instruction.1: Place your palm flush against the wall.
Instruction.2: Take one step forward and straighten your arm slowly to extend your bicep.
Instruction.3: Hold at the peak of the stretch.
Instruction.4: Return to starting position.

Instruction.1: Stand straight with the plate held at your side
Instruction.2: Keep your hips and shoulders facing forward, bend to one side slowly
Instruction.3: Return to the upright position.
Instruction.4: Switch hands and repeat

Instruction.1: Stand tall holding two plates in each hand with a pinch grip.
Instruction.2: Walk for the desired distance or time.

Instruction.1: Stand facing the plate with your feet shoulder-width apart and the plate positioned between your feet.
Instruction.2: Bend down and grasp the plate from the top edges with both hands, making sure your thumbs and fingers are evenly spaced.
Instruction.3: Keep your back straight, chest up and core engaged, and stand up with the plate, keeping it close to your body.
Instruction.4: Lower the plate back down to the ground, keeping control and maintaining good posture.

Instruction.1: Make sure to keep your elbow close to your body and your core engaged throughout the movement.
Instruction.2: Bend forward at your hips while maintaining a flat back.
Instruction.3: Pull the plate toward your upper abdomen.
Instruction.4: Lower the weight in a controlled manner and repeat.

WorkoutName: Plate Single Leg Pinch Grip Deadlift

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and facing forwards. Grip the sides of a weight plate with your palms facing down.
Instruction.2: Balance on one foot, as you raise the weight keep your arms and back straight, while you bring your  other foot back towards the ground
Instruction.3: Keep four raised leg straight and in alignment with your back as you lower the plate back down to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and holding two plates with a pinch grip.
Instruction.2: Place one foot slightly behind the other, with the heel of your back foot elevated.
Instruction.3: From this starting position, bend at the hips and knees to lower the plates towards the ground, keeping your back straight and your core engaged.

Instruction.1: Lay underneath a fixed horizontal bar and grab the bar with a wide overhand grip. Place a plate on your chest.
Instruction.2: Pull your body straight up to the bar.
Instruction.3: Return to the starting position, your arms fully extended. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Grab the bar shoulder width apart with a supinated grip (palms facing you). Use a dip belt and the let the weight hang between your legs.
Instruction.2: With your body hanging and arms fully extended, pull yourself up until your chin is past the bar.
Instruction.3: Slowly return to starting position. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Attach weight to yourself using a dip belt. Grip a pull-up bar with palms facing forward.
Instruction.2: Hang with arms fully extended.
Instruction.3: Hold for recommended amount of time, keeping your core engaged.

Instruction.1: Lay underneath a fixed horizontal bar and grab the bar with a wide overhand grip.
Instruction.2: Pull your body straight up to the bar.
Instruction.3: Return to the starting position, your arms fully extended. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Grip the dumbbell with your palm facing upwards with your forearm rested against the bench.
Instruction.2: Slowly curl your wrist upwards in a semicircular motion.
Instruction.3: Return to starting position and repeat.

Instruction.1: Grab two dumbbells with an overhand grip and lay your forearms across your knees.
Instruction.2: Let your wrists flex fully, then extend your wrists.

Instruction.1: Grab the dumbbells with a pronated (overhand) grip. You can do this exercise thumbless if it's more comfortable on your wrists.
Instruction.2: Flex at the elbows until your biceps touch your forearms. Try not to let your elbows flair outward.

Instruction.1: Brace your off arm against something stable (bench, box). Stagger your stance so your leg on the side of your working arm is back.
Instruction.2: Try to get your torso to parallel with the ground. That will extend your range of motion.
Instruction.3: Let your arm hang freely and then pull your elbow back. Imagine you've got a tennis ball in your armpit and squeeze it each rep.

Instruction.1: Lay on an incline bench.
Instruction.2: Grab the dumbbells with a pronated (overhand) grip. You can do this exercise thumbless if it's more comfortable on your wrists.
Instruction.3: Flex at the elbows until your biceps touch your forearms. Try not to let your elbows flair outward.

Instruction.1: Lay on an incline bench with your palms facing forward.
Instruction.2: Flex at the elbows until your forearms touch your biceps.
Instruction.3: When you hit the top of the movement, rotate your palms and then lower the dumbbells slowly.

Instruction.1: Grip the dumbbell with your palm facing upwards with your forearm rested against the bench.
Instruction.2: Slowly curl your wrist upwards in a semicircular motion.
Instruction.3: Return to starting position and repeat.

WorkoutName: Dumbbell Single Arm Bench Wrist Curl

Instruction.1: Drape one arm over a bench while holding a dumbbell. Point your palm toward the ceiling.
Instruction.2: Extend and curl your wrist against resistance.

Instruction.1: Sit by a bench or table and lean your arm on it.
Instruction.2: Hold a dumbbell/weight/lever on one end.
Instruction.3: Rotate the wrist so the palm faces down and up in succession.

Instruction.1: Grab the bar shoulder width apart with a supinated grip (palms facing you). Use a dip belt and the let the weight hang between your legs.
Instruction.2: With your body hanging and arms fully extended, pull yourself up until your chin is past the bar.
Instruction.3: Slowly return to starting position. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Grab a dumbbell in each hand, arms straight down.
Instruction.2: Walk forward with a straight posture.

WorkoutName: Dumbbell Bench Braced Reverse Incline Curl

Instruction.1: Lay off the side of a bench and place the back off your arms on the edge of your bench. Keep your hips lowered toward the floor.
Instruction.2: Take an overhand grip. Fully extend your elbows and then flex the elbows.
Instruction.3: Lay off the side of a bench and place the back off your arms on the edge of your bench. Keep your hips lowered toward the floor.
Instruction.4: Take an overhand grip. Fully extend your elbows and then flex the elbows.

WorkoutName: Dumbbell Single Arm Bench Braced Reverse Incline Curl

Instruction.1: Lay off the side of a bench and place the back off your arms on the edge of your bench. Keep your hips lowered toward the floor.
Instruction.2: Take an overhand grip. Fully extend your elbows and then flex the elbows.

Instruction.1: Grab two dumbbells with an overhand grip and lay your forearms across a bench.
Instruction.2: Let your wrists flex fully, then extend your wrists.

Instruction.1: Use a handle attachment. The cable should be set all the way to the bottom of the machine.
Instruction.2: Face away from the cable machine. Stagger your stance so you have a better base of support.
Instruction.3: Start with your elbow at a 90° angle with your palm facing up. Flex and extend at the wrist.

Instruction.1: Use a handle attachment. The cable should be set all the way to the bottom of the machine.
Instruction.2: Face away from the cable machine. Stagger your stance so you have a better base of support.
Instruction.3: Start with your elbow at a 90 degree angle with your palm facing down. Flex and extend at the wrist.

Instruction.1: Use a handle attachment. The cable should be set all the way to the bottom of the machine.
Instruction.2: Face away from the cable machine. Stagger your stance so you have a better base of support.
Instruction.3: Face your palm downwards. Flex at the elbow and extend.

Instruction.1: Use a bar attachment. The cable should be set all the way to the bottom of the machine.
Instruction.2: Face the cable machine.
Instruction.3: Stagger your stance so you have a better base of support. Face your palm down. Flex at the elbow and extend.

Instruction.1: Use a handle attachment. The cable should be set all the way to the bottom of the machine.
Instruction.2: Face away from the cable machine and sit on the bench. Stagger your stance so you have a better base of support.
Instruction.3: Face your palm downwards. Flex at the elbow and extend.

Instruction.1: Use a handle attachment. The cable should be set all the way to the bottom of the machine.
Instruction.2: Face away from the cable machine. Stagger your stance so you have a better base of support.
Instruction.3: Face your palm downwards. Flex at the elbow and extend.

Instruction.1: Stand facing the TRX straps and grasp the handles with both hands, palms facing away from your body.
Instruction.2: Walk back until the straps are taut, keeping your arms straight.
Instruction.3: Slowly curl your hands towards your shoulders, keeping your elbows close to your body.

Instruction.1: Hold bosu and hinge forward.
Instruction.2: Pull bosu towards chest, squeezing shoulder blades.

Instruction.1: Take an overhand grip.
Instruction.2: Keep your knees mostly extended and hinge forward at the hips.
Instruction.3: Keep a flat back.

Instruction.1: Hold a neutral grip.
Instruction.2: Flex your elbows until your forearms touch your biceps.
Instruction.3: Extend your elbows fully to finish each rep.

WorkoutName: Crosslateral Core Stabilisation Unilateral Load Kettlebell

Instruction.1: Begin by standing with your feet hip-width apart and holding a kettlebell at one side of your body, with your palms facing your thighs.
Instruction.2: Hing forward with a flat back and lift the kettlebell.
Instruction.3: Hold the kettlebell at your side and make sure to not lean to one side.

Instruction.1: Drape your forearm over a bench.
Instruction.2: Hold a dumbbell in a neutral wrist position with your palm facing downwards.

Instruction.1: Kneel by a bench placing the arm you want to mobilise on, palm facing down.
Instruction.2: Bring a massage ball to the top of your forearm and move it around applying gentle pressure.
Instruction.3: Find the right/sore spot.
Instruction.4: You can move your wrist in various directions in order to mobilise your wrist extensors.

Instruction.1: Raise one arm keeping your shoulder relaxed.
Instruction.2: Hold the back of your palm with the other hand and passively flex the wrist.
Instruction.3: You should feel a stretch on the top part of your arm.

Instruction.1: Bring one arm in front of you palm facing up, elbow straight and shoulder relaxed.
Instruction.2: With your other hand hold onto the palm and force it into passive extension.
Instruction.3: This will stretch your wrist flexors.

Instruction.1: Stand up straight holding a dowel/lever/weight in one hand.
Instruction.2: Hold the weight so it points behind you and towards the ground.
Instruction.3: Squeeze your grip to raise the weight.

Instruction.1: Lay underneath a fixed horizontal bar and grab the bar with a wide overhand grip.
Instruction.2: Pull your body straight up to the bar.
Instruction.3: Return to the starting position, your arms fully extended. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Grab the bar shoulder width apart with a supinated grip (palms facing you)
Instruction.2: With your body hanging and arms fully extended, pull yourself up until your chin is past the bar.
Instruction.3: Slowly return to starting position. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Lay underneath a fixed horizontal bar and grab the bar with a wide overhand grip.
Instruction.2: Pull your body straight up to the bar.
Instruction.3: Return to the starting position, your arms fully extended. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Grab a door frame or a rack and place your feet near the frame.
Instruction.2: Start with your elbows extended, row your body towards your hands.
Instruction.3: Return to the starting position, your arms fully extended. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Lay underneath a fixed horizontal bar and grab the bar with an underhand grip.
Instruction.2: Pull your body straight up to the bar.
Instruction.3: Return to the starting position, your arms fully extended. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Grip a pull-up bar with palms facing forward.
Instruction.2: Hang with arms fully extended.
Instruction.3: Hold for recommended amount of time, keeping your core engaged.

Instruction.1: Hang from a bar with arms fully extended.
Instruction.2: Lift legs to form an "L" shape.
Instruction.3: Hold for allotted amount of time keeping your abs flexed.

Instruction.1: Grab the bar shoulder width apart with a supinated grip (palms facing you)
Instruction.2: With your body in an "L" position and arms fully extended, pull yourself up until your chin is past the bar.
Instruction.3: Slowly return to starting position. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Grab the bar shoulder width apart with a supinated grip (palms facing you)
Instruction.2: With your body hanging and arms fully extended, pull yourself up and lean backwards. Try to touch your chest to the bar.
Instruction.3: Slowly return to starting position. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Grab the rings shoulder width apart with a supinated grip (palms facing you)
Instruction.2: With your body hanging and arms fully extended, pull yourself up until your chin is past the rings.
Instruction.3: Slowly return to starting position. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Grab the rings shoulder width apart with a pronated grip (palms facing away).
Instruction.2: With your body hanging and arms fully extended, pull yourself up and rotate your fists until your chin is past the rings.
Instruction.3: Slowly return to starting position. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Hold two kettlebells in each hand.
Instruction.2: Keep your shoulders blades pulled back and walk for a specified duration.

Instruction.1: Stand up straight with a kettlebell in both hands in front of your pelvis, with your forearms facing inwards.
Instruction.2: Flex your wrist upwards until wrists are fully extended.
Instruction.3: Lower to the starting position and repeat.

Instruction.1: Stand up straight with a kettlebell in both hands in front of your pelvis, with your forearms facing outwards.
Instruction.2: Flex your wrist towards your body until the kettlebell is level with your stomach.
Instruction.3: Lower to the starting position and repeat.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet hip-width apart.
Instruction.2: Hold kettlebell with palms facing down.
Instruction.3: Lift kettlebell toward shoulders, squeezing biceps, then lower with control.

Instruction.1: Grip the kettlebells with your palm facing upwards with your forearm rested against the bench.
Instruction.2: Slowly curl your wrist upwards in a semicircular motion.
Instruction.3: Return to starting position and repeat.

Instruction.1: Stand tall holding two kettlebells in each hand.
Instruction.2: March in place for the desired amount of reps or time.

Instruction.1: Standing straight with a kettlebell in one hand, lift the knee of one leg off the floor to knee height.
Instruction.2: Bring the leg back to standing and repeat with the other leg, keeping the kettlebell on the same side.
Instruction.3: Repeat.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet hip-width apart.
Instruction.2: Hold a kettlebell with palms facing down.
Instruction.3: Lift kettlebell toward shoulders, squeezing biceps, then lower with control.

Instruction.1: Standing straight with kettlebells, start walking towards a set point. Pulling your knee up toward the ceiling.
Instruction.2: Make sure to keep your chest tall and shoulder blades pulled back.
Instruction.3: Try to keep your stride distance roughly the same.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder width apart holding the kettlebell with both hands in front of your thighs.
Instruction.2: Bend forward at the hips bringing the kettlebell to the floor while you slightly bend your knees, keeping your back straight.
Instruction.3: Lift the kettlebell upwards towards your chest and lower - repeat.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder width apart, shifting one foot behind you. Hold the kettlebell in the same hand as the leg shifted backwards.
Instruction.2: Bend forwards at the hips bringing the kettlebell to the floor while you slightly bend your knee, keeping your back straight.
Instruction.3: Lift the kettlebell upwards towards your chest and lower - repeat.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, kettlebell in one hand.
Instruction.2: Bend at hips, row kettlebell to chest.
Instruction.3: Alternate hands for each row.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, hold a kettlebell in each hand.
Instruction.2: Hinge at hips, keep back straight, and pull both kettlebells to hips.

WorkoutName: Kettlebell Single Arm Row On Bench

Instruction.1: Start by standing in front of a flat bench with your feet shoulder-width apart and holding a kettlebell in one hand.
Instruction.2: Place your other hand on the bench for support, and bend at the waist so that your chest is parallel to the ground.
Instruction.3: From this starting position, row the kettlebell up towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blade together as you do so.
Instruction.4: Make sure to keep your elbow close to your body and your core engaged throughout the movement.

Instruction.1: Standing straight with a kettlebell in one hand, walk for a specified distance or duration.
Instruction.2: Stay upright and don't lean to one side.

Instruction.1: Grab two kettlebells with an overhand grip and lay your forearms across a bench.
Instruction.2: Let your wrists flex fully, then extend your wrists.

Instruction.1: Begin by standing with your feet hip-width apart and holding a kettlebell at one side of your body, with your palms facing your thighs.
Instruction.2: Keeping your core engaged and your back straight, bend at the hips and knees to lower the kettlebell down towards the ground.
Instruction.3: As the kettlebell reaches the ground, use your legs and glutes to push through your heels and extend your hips and knees to raise your body back to the starting position.
Instruction.4: Repeat the movement for the desired number of reps, then switch sides and repeat the exercise with the kettlebell on the opposite side of your body.

Instruction.1: Attach band to a low anchor point. Use a neutral grip.
Instruction.2: Flex your elbow until you feel your biceps contract. Then fully extend elbows.

Instruction.1: Attach band to a low anchor point. . Point your palms toward your thighs.
Instruction.2: Flex your elbow until you feel your biceps contract. Then fully extend elbows.

Instruction.1: Start with a band attached to a high point, your feet staggered, and an overhand grip.
Instruction.2: Flex your elbows pulling your forearms to your biceps. Your fists should land by your forehead.

Instruction.1: Start by standing on the center of the band with both feet, shoulder-width apart.
Instruction.2: Hold the band with both hands, palms facing down, arms extended straight in front of you.
Instruction.3: Slowly curl your hands towards your shoulders, pulling the band tight, then lower your arms back to the starting position, keeping tension on the band throughout the exercise.

Instruction.1: Start in a tabletop position on your hands and knees with your hands directly under your shoulders and your knees directly under your hips.
Instruction.2: Turn your hands so that your fingers are pointing towards the sides of your mat and the tops of your hands are on the floor.
Instruction.3: Keep your arms straight and your shoulders away from your ears.
Instruction.4: Hold the pose for several breaths or as long as is comfortable.

Instruction.1: Start in a tabletop position on your hands and knees with your hands directly under your shoulders and your knees directly under your hips.
Instruction.2: Turn your hands so that your fingers are pointing towards your knees and the tops of your hands are on the floor.
Instruction.3: Keep your arms straight and your shoulders away from your ears.
Instruction.4: Hold the pose for several breaths or as long as is comfortable.

Instruction.1: Come onto your hands and knees on the mat with your wrists directly under your shoulders and your knees under your hips.
Instruction.2: Turn your palms down and spread your fingers wide, with your fingertips pointing towards your knees.
Instruction.3: Press into your palms and extend your arms fully to lift your shoulders away from your ears.
Instruction.4: Hold the pose for a few breaths, and then release by slowly lowering your hands to the mat and coming back to a neutral tabletop position.

Instruction.1: Begin in a kneeling position with your knees together and your shins and feet on the floor.
Instruction.2: Sit back on your heels and place your palms face down on your thighs, with your fingers pointing towards your knees.
Instruction.3: Relax your shoulders and take deep breaths.
Instruction.4: Hold the pose for several breaths or as long as is comfortable.
